2
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:53,053
DEAR X

3
00:00:53,636 --> 00:00:55,722
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, AND EVENTS
IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

4
00:00:55,805 --> 00:00:57,182
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED
WITH GUARDIANS PRESENT

5
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:08,109
BUSAN INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL

6
00:01:12,822 --> 00:01:16,576
Here comes actor Heo In-gang
on the red carpet.

7
00:01:16,659 --> 00:01:19,162
He will be presenting
the Best Actor Award tonight

8
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:21,247
at the Busan International
Film Festival.

9
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:22,999
Please welcome him
with a big round of applause.

10
00:02:29,649 --> 00:02:30,650
Take my hand.

11
00:02:41,452 --> 00:02:46,833
Baek Ah-jin is now walking in
gracefully with Heo In-gang's escort.

12
00:02:46,916 --> 00:02:49,085
As one of the most promising
next-generation stars

13
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:51,713
leading the future of Korean cinema

14
00:02:51,796 --> 00:02:54,924
Baek Ah-jin captivates everyone
with poise and elegance

15
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:56,509
rarely seen in a rookie actor.

16
00:02:58,303 --> 00:03:02,891
The two are walking down the carpet
dazzling under the camera flashes.

17
00:03:02,974 --> 00:03:05,268
Please give them a warm welcome.

18
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:09,564
Hello, In-gang.

19
00:03:09,647 --> 00:03:10,648
Hello.

20
00:03:10,732 --> 00:03:15,361
You're the most coveted star in film
and advertising worldwide right now.

21
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:18,740
Everyone in the country is curious
to see just how far

22
00:03:18,823 --> 00:03:21,951
your fame and success will go.

23
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:23,745
How does it feel?

24
00:03:25,246 --> 00:03:28,875
It really sinks in
now that I'm here at the BIFF.

25
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:33,171
And here with superstar Heo In-gang
is Baek Ah-jin.

26
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:36,007
Hello, I'm Baek Ah-jin.

27
00:03:41,512 --> 00:03:44,933
You must be nervous about being
on the red carpet for the first time.

28
00:03:45,475 --> 00:03:48,019
Yes, I was very nervous

29
00:03:48,102 --> 00:03:53,358
but thanks to In-gang's
advice and guidance

30
00:03:53,441 --> 00:03:54,901
I've relaxed a little.

31
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:57,987
I think I'll be able
to enjoy the night

32
00:03:58,613 --> 00:04:00,198
with a happy heart.

33
00:04:00,281 --> 00:04:02,909
Then, you should stay
close by his side tonight.

34
00:04:02,992 --> 00:04:05,787
But did you get permission from Lena?

35
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:11,125
Oh, Lena and I
are really close friends.

36
00:04:11,209 --> 00:04:14,587
And she's a generous person

37
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:16,673
so I'm sure she'll understand.

38
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:48,788
Did I wake you?

39
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:50,415
Sorry.

40
00:04:50,873 --> 00:04:52,959
I wanted to have a drink
with you tonight.

41
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,380
You're the best.

42
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,844
I told you to stop
coming to my place.

43
00:05:08,349 --> 00:05:10,351
Then why didn't you change
the door code?

44
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:14,856
I know you don't mean it.

45
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:23,990
Oh, right.

46
00:05:24,532 --> 00:05:26,242
Is this the hand that Ah-jin held?

47
00:05:27,118 --> 00:05:28,286
I'll disinfect it for you.

48
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:30,121
Here we go.

49
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:33,708
It was Mi-ri's favor.

50
00:05:39,922 --> 00:05:41,924
You mean Baek Ah-jin's favor.

51
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:44,093
Did you see the look in her eyes?

52
00:05:44,677 --> 00:05:45,928
They're so creepy.

53
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:50,350
She acts innocent, polite,
and sweet to everyone

54
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:52,560
but I get chills
when I look into her eyes.

55
00:05:52,643 --> 00:05:55,063
I can't tell
what emotions she's feeling.

56
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:57,899
Lena, how much longer
do I have to wait?

57
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:01,611
Wait for what?

58
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:05,156
About when I broke up with you?

59
00:06:05,239 --> 00:06:07,283
You know I didn't mean that!

60
00:06:07,909 --> 00:06:08,910
Why would you...

61
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:13,414
I've done this countless times.
Why won't you let it slide this time?

62
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:16,667
I thought I was being considerate
by waiting for you to accept it.

63
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:21,297
But maybe my kindness
gave you false hope.

64
00:06:22,215 --> 00:06:23,216
Baby.

65
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:34,560
Baby.

66
00:06:35,686 --> 00:06:37,605
Baby, I'm sorry.

67
00:06:39,482 --> 00:06:43,069
I'll be so lonely without you.

68
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:45,738
Can you give me one more chance?

69
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:47,323
I'll try harder.

70
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:50,618
It's all my fault. I'm sorry.

71
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:03,589
I'll pretend I didn't hear that.

72
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:07,051
Bye.

73
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:09,554
Sleep tight.

74
00:07:18,604 --> 00:07:20,648
Please help me.

75
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:26,529
What's going on?

76
00:07:27,196 --> 00:07:28,614
Cut! Lena!

77
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:30,491
Director.

78
00:07:30,575 --> 00:07:32,243
Her acting is completely off.

79
00:07:35,371 --> 00:07:37,665
Hey, what's with that cheesy acting?

80
00:07:38,374 --> 00:07:39,417
Didn't you rehearse it?

81
00:07:40,251 --> 00:07:41,252
I'm sorry.

82
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:45,381
I wouldn't make that face
even if a cockroach were chasing me.

83
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:48,176
She's right, Ah-jin.
This isn't a difficult scene.

84
00:07:48,551 --> 00:07:51,053
Hyang-i, get me a bottle of water.
I'm thirsty.

85
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:52,597
Just a moment.

86
00:07:53,181 --> 00:07:54,182
Hey.

87
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:55,808
Go get it now.

88
00:07:55,892 --> 00:07:57,852
But Ah-jin might catch a cold.

89
00:07:58,269 --> 00:07:59,270
Now.

90
00:08:02,064 --> 00:08:03,065
Okay.

91
00:08:04,942 --> 00:08:06,194
Let's take five.

92
00:08:07,236 --> 00:08:08,362
Take three!

93
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:11,657
Help.

94
00:08:12,408 --> 00:08:13,409
Please help.

95
00:08:14,118 --> 00:08:15,244
Take five!

96
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:18,080
- Ready.
- Take ten!

97
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:23,127
Please help me.

98
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:24,462
- Take 12!
- Take 15!

99
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:26,339
- Take 20!
- Please help.

100
00:08:29,634 --> 00:08:31,093
This is nuts.

101
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:38,017
Are you glaring at me now?
Your eyes could cut steel.

102
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:40,728
Director, did you see
the look in her eyes?

103
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:43,481
How am I supposed to act
when she looks at me like that?

104
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:45,149
Lena!

105
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:47,735
Let's not make this harder, okay?

106
00:08:49,695 --> 00:08:51,531
I can't get into character at all.

107
00:08:53,115 --> 00:08:54,116
Can I just go home?

108
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:55,785
This is too much.

109
00:08:57,745 --> 00:08:59,497
I've never seen anyone like her.

110
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:03,876
You know why
she's acting like that, right?

111
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:08,923
I suggest you just apologize
and smooth it over.

112
00:09:09,632 --> 00:09:10,883
She's your senior, after all.

113
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:13,094
If we shut down this shoot today

114
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,846
we'll lose a fortune.

115
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:19,100
Please, I'm begging you.

116
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:21,269
I'm sorry, Director.

117
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:23,813
I'll do better.

118
00:09:26,482 --> 00:09:28,401
We have zero chemistry.

119
00:09:28,943 --> 00:09:30,486
I can't get into the scene with her.

120
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:37,702
Why does everyone act
like I'm doing it on purpose?

121
00:09:38,119 --> 00:09:39,412
Why would I do that?

122
00:09:45,459 --> 00:09:46,544
BAEK AH-JIN REPLACES LENA
FOR JIN SOJU

123
00:09:46,627 --> 00:09:49,547
COSMETICS MARKET SLOWS,
YET THE BAEK AH-JIN EFFECT PERSISTS

124
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:50,631
A GUARANTEE OF SUCCESS?

125
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:57,179
Hey, In-gang, you're here.

126
00:09:58,931 --> 00:10:01,851
Thanks for going
to the film festival with Ah-jin.

127
00:10:07,773 --> 00:10:10,276
I helped you out,
so it's your turn now.

128
00:10:10,359 --> 00:10:11,527
What is it?

129
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:14,739
You must know, but I broke up
with Lena a long time ago.

130
00:10:15,698 --> 00:10:18,868
She couldn't accept it
and needed time to process

131
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:20,536
but this can't go on.

132
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:22,872
I need you to help end it.

133
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:24,498
In-gang.

134
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:28,127
The Hadere deal is almost signed.

135
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:29,795
Just wait a little longer.

136
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:32,673
Hadere requires
real couples as models.

137
00:10:33,049 --> 00:10:35,009
No matter how much money's involved

138
00:10:35,092 --> 00:10:36,969
I don't want to lie to the public.

139
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:40,389
I know how you feel.

140
00:10:41,098 --> 00:10:42,183
I really do.

141
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:45,978
But could you think about it
once more?

142
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:47,980
I've done everything you asked.

143
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:51,233
But this time, I really can't.

144
00:10:54,362 --> 00:10:55,363
All right, then.

145
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:57,531
I'm leaving.

146
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:00,534
Right.

147
00:11:00,618 --> 00:11:03,579
Look after Ah-jin
during next week's shoot.

148
00:11:03,829 --> 00:11:06,082
She's new and doesn't know much yet.

149
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:09,669
Treat her like family, okay?

150
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,338
Bye.

151
00:11:21,597 --> 00:11:22,598
Hey.

152
00:11:24,016 --> 00:11:25,017
Lena did what?

153
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:46,080
Do you think I'm a child?

154
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:48,582
Don't try to calm me down
with cheap candy.

155
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:52,086
Do you think
all I've got for you is candy?

156
00:11:52,169 --> 00:11:53,713
Drunk driving.

157
00:11:54,463 --> 00:11:56,090
Switching drivers afterward.

158
00:11:56,549 --> 00:11:59,885
If that comes out,
your career is over.

159
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:09,186
Mi-ri!

160
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:10,479
Wait, I'm sorry.

161
00:12:14,650 --> 00:12:15,651
Thanks.

162
00:12:18,863 --> 00:12:20,656
Mi-ri, I was wrong.

163
00:12:21,949 --> 00:12:22,950
Lena!

164
00:12:24,785 --> 00:12:26,203
Please think.

165
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:27,872
Okay?

166
00:12:27,955 --> 00:12:30,958
I knew she'd get what's coming.

167
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:33,085
Even if it's Ms. Seo

168
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:36,338
I still don't understand
how Lena acts that way.

169
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:38,299
There's always a reason.

170
00:12:38,382 --> 00:12:40,801
Ms. Seo has been
in this industry for years.

171
00:12:40,885 --> 00:12:44,138
This won't be her first time
handling someone as arrogant as Lena.

172
00:12:44,221 --> 00:12:46,223
She prepares everything in advance.

173
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:49,852
Mi-ri, you can't just
leave like that.

174
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:51,562
Prepare for what?

175
00:12:53,397 --> 00:12:54,648
I've heard about it.

176
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:57,902
She keeps a file that works
as shackles on every actor.

177
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:00,696
Stuff that could ruin
not just their careers

178
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:03,199
but also their lives if revealed.

179
00:13:03,699 --> 00:13:06,368
You'd think it's a rumor

180
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:08,120
but when I look at Lena like that

181
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:09,830
- Mi-ri!
- it may not be a rumor.

182
00:13:10,164 --> 00:13:11,582
Oh, jeez.

183
00:13:11,665 --> 00:13:12,917
Mi-ri, please.

184
00:13:13,334 --> 00:13:15,336
- She really asked for it.
- Gosh.

185
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:34,438
EPISODE 5: GRANT ME THE POWER
TO RISE TO THE TOP

186
00:14:04,635 --> 00:14:05,928
Makeup looks great today.

187
00:14:06,887 --> 00:14:08,973
Your face did it all, Ah-jin.

188
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:18,691
Oh, right.
We even go to the same salon.

189
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:22,152
We have so much in common.

190
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:24,029
One would think
we were a package deal.

191
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:25,823
You're even making me look bad.

192
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:28,534
Get me something to drink.

193
00:14:29,034 --> 00:14:31,829
While you're at it,
give us the room for five minutes.

194
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:33,414
Sure.

195
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:38,252
I wonder why you irritate me so much.

196
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:40,629
Why do you think that is?

197
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:42,214
Well, I also wonder

198
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:44,633
why you absolutely despise me.

199
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:49,722
Rookie, you should be thinking
of a reason, not asking me.

200
00:14:50,347 --> 00:14:52,182
You should very well know

201
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:55,477
the film festival pairing was
Ms. Seo's decision.

202
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:56,770
It wasn't something I could refuse--

203
00:14:56,854 --> 00:14:59,106
And you wanted to refuse?

204
00:15:00,107 --> 00:15:01,108
No.

205
00:15:02,359 --> 00:15:04,069
I'd be a fool to refuse.

206
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:06,447
I had no reason to turn it down.

207
00:15:08,991 --> 00:15:10,576
It was such a good opportunity.

208
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:14,371
Do you think you're untouchable
because Mi-ri is backing you?

209
00:15:18,375 --> 00:15:19,376
Lena.

210
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:23,589
What dirt does she have on you
that makes you tremble like that?

211
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:27,134
Hyang-i turned herself in
and said it was her fault.

212
00:15:27,217 --> 00:15:30,012
You're just here to give a statement,
so watch what you say.

213
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:31,138
Have a nice day.

214
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:36,060
I've been so curious
that I've lost sleep over this.

215
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,730
Would you tell me, too?

216
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:41,482
You.

217
00:15:43,734 --> 00:15:45,402
Don't ask me for reasons.

218
00:15:45,486 --> 00:15:46,654
Look for the reasons...

219
00:15:48,656 --> 00:15:50,699
in yourself.

220
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:53,577
That's the only way
you won't be replaced next time.

221
00:15:55,412 --> 00:15:56,830
Ah-jin, are you heading out?

222
00:15:57,623 --> 00:16:00,125
My manager's waiting downstairs.
See you.

223
00:16:01,001 --> 00:16:02,002
Bye.

224
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:10,678
That bitch.

225
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:20,604
Delivery.

226
00:17:37,639 --> 00:17:39,850
If and when you become
more useful than you are now

227
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:41,727
I might have a use for you.

228
00:17:42,352 --> 00:17:43,729
Then we could meet again.

229
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:54,531
Man.

230
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:04,374
I really missed you.

231
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:28,524
Hyang-i, you said
you used to be Lena's manager, right?

232
00:18:28,607 --> 00:18:29,608
Yes.

233
00:18:30,150 --> 00:18:33,195
Is that why she mistreats you?

234
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:35,906
Who knows what's in her head?

235
00:18:36,448 --> 00:18:38,408
I thought I did my best.

236
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:39,910
Why do you ask?

237
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:42,788
Because you're my manager now.

238
00:18:43,914 --> 00:18:46,416
Imagine how I'll feel
if anyone talks down to you.

239
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:50,462
Especially Lena.
She already hates me.

240
00:18:51,004 --> 00:18:53,423
Maybe that's why
she takes it out on you.

241
00:18:53,924 --> 00:18:58,512
If she ever does that again,
make sure to tell me, okay?

242
00:18:58,595 --> 00:18:59,638
Don't worry.

243
00:18:59,721 --> 00:19:02,057
Remember the shackle file
I mentioned last time?

244
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:05,644
I asked around, and they said
Ms. Seo keeps it in her desk drawer.

245
00:19:05,894 --> 00:19:07,521
If things go south,
we can just take that.

246
00:19:15,696 --> 00:19:16,697
Hyang-i.

247
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:21,660
We're the same age.
Why do you keep using the honorifics?

248
00:19:23,620 --> 00:19:25,622
You can drop it when it's just us.

249
00:19:26,957 --> 00:19:27,958
You sure?

250
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:42,014
YOON SEOK-HA'S FIRST BOOK SIGNING

251
00:19:42,097 --> 00:19:43,390
CO-OFFENDER Y

252
00:19:43,473 --> 00:19:44,975
A JOURNEY THROUGH STORIES
WITH AUTHOR YOON SEOK-HA

253
00:19:45,058 --> 00:19:47,102
NUMBER 1 BESTSELLER FOR 7 WEEKS

254
00:19:47,186 --> 00:19:48,937
WINNER OF THE 2021
LITERARY SQUARE NOVEL AWARD

255
00:20:19,176 --> 00:20:20,969
Get out right now!

256
00:20:21,053 --> 00:20:22,262
How dare you come here?

257
00:20:23,263 --> 00:20:24,514
Father.

258
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:27,726
Do you think I'd come here
if I had any other choice?

259
00:20:27,809 --> 00:20:29,186
Don't "Father" me!

260
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:32,773
I warned you not to jump
into a business you can't handle.

261
00:20:32,856 --> 00:20:34,733
Now you took out loan-shark money?

262
00:20:34,816 --> 00:20:36,568
Are you out of your mind?

263
00:20:36,652 --> 00:20:38,946
Would I be here
if I were in my right mind?

264
00:20:39,821 --> 00:20:40,822
Father.

265
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:43,200
I feel like I'm going to die.

266
00:20:43,784 --> 00:20:46,828
People shouldn't have to die
over money.

267
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:49,373
Help me out this once--

268
00:20:49,456 --> 00:20:50,874
You think I don't know you?

269
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:52,626
Get out
if you're here to spew nonsense.

270
00:20:52,709 --> 00:20:54,294
I can't stand the sight of you.

271
00:20:57,631 --> 00:21:01,969
Then I'll go to Jun-seo and beg him.
Is that what you want?

272
00:21:02,594 --> 00:21:04,179
What did you say?

273
00:21:05,222 --> 00:21:06,890
How dare you--

274
00:21:06,974 --> 00:21:09,726
It's not like you can take
that money with you when you die!

275
00:21:12,187 --> 00:21:14,147
Let's be honest.

276
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:17,109
I'm his mother.
I have the right to ask him for this.

277
00:21:17,192 --> 00:21:20,362
I raised your precious grandson
with these hands!

278
00:21:20,862 --> 00:21:23,740
I raised the child that you dote on

279
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:26,994
but you won't spare a single penny
for the daughter-in-law?

280
00:21:27,661 --> 00:21:28,787
Does that make sense?

281
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:32,374
Soo-hyuk, get her out now.

282
00:21:32,624 --> 00:21:33,625
Ma'am, let's go.

283
00:21:34,001 --> 00:21:35,168
I'm not going anywhere.

284
00:21:35,252 --> 00:21:36,253
- Calm down.
- Get off me.

285
00:21:36,336 --> 00:21:38,380
- This way.
- You can't do this to me.

286
00:21:38,463 --> 00:21:40,173
You'll be punished for this!

287
00:21:40,257 --> 00:21:41,842
Let go of me!

288
00:21:42,509 --> 00:21:43,510
Father!

289
00:21:55,272 --> 00:21:58,191
How long has she been coming here?

290
00:21:58,483 --> 00:21:59,901
It's none of your concern.

291
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:01,987
Is this all the books you brought?

292
00:22:02,070 --> 00:22:05,741
This won't even cover
a fraction of my contacts.

293
00:22:05,824 --> 00:22:07,951
Next time, bring a whole bundle.

294
00:22:16,043 --> 00:22:17,544
NAMYEONG BANK

295
00:22:22,424 --> 00:22:23,884
I gave you my account number.

296
00:22:24,593 --> 00:22:26,553
Do you have to show up at the house?

297
00:22:27,054 --> 00:22:29,348
You know your uncle will flip
if he finds out.

298
00:22:29,890 --> 00:22:31,141
- Auntie, I just--
- Sure.

299
00:22:32,059 --> 00:22:34,770
I get that you want to help
your little brother.

300
00:22:34,853 --> 00:22:36,229
I won't stop you from doing that.

301
00:22:36,855 --> 00:22:38,482
But put yourself in his shoes.

302
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:43,278
Who would want to see a brother
who killed their own dad?

303
00:22:47,324 --> 00:22:49,576
Why do you have to make me
say these things?

304
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:58,001
I get it, so don't worry.

305
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:01,505
I'll transfer the money next time.

306
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:14,601
Auntie.

307
00:23:15,852 --> 00:23:18,230
You'll keep sending me
Jae-hun's photos, right?

308
00:23:20,399 --> 00:23:22,275
I heard he's doing
great in school, unlike me.

309
00:23:22,359 --> 00:23:26,363
If he wins any awards
or gets good grades, send them to me.

310
00:23:29,741 --> 00:23:30,784
Thank you

311
00:23:32,035 --> 00:23:33,161
for not abandoning him

312
00:23:34,204 --> 00:23:35,288
and raising him well.

313
00:23:38,291 --> 00:23:39,292
And I'm sorry.

314
00:23:40,544 --> 00:23:41,753
I'll spend the rest of my life

315
00:23:42,838 --> 00:23:44,548
making it up to you.

316
00:23:48,885 --> 00:23:51,346
So, don't cry over being harsh to me.

317
00:23:52,889 --> 00:23:53,890
Just be happy.

318
00:23:54,975 --> 00:23:56,101
Okay?

319
00:24:41,938 --> 00:24:43,106
Auntie, I'm home.

320
00:24:59,831 --> 00:25:01,958
Hello, please take
good care of In-gang.

321
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:03,877
- Thank you.
- Grab some snacks.

322
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:06,004
Isn't he amazing?
Please take good care of him.

323
00:25:06,087 --> 00:25:07,172
- Thanks for the snacks.
- Sure.

324
00:25:07,255 --> 00:25:08,882
- Help yourselves.
- Thank you.

325
00:25:08,965 --> 00:25:10,091
Hi!

326
00:25:12,344 --> 00:25:13,553
Have some coffee.

327
00:25:13,637 --> 00:25:16,431
- It's on me today.
- Thank you so much.

328
00:25:16,515 --> 00:25:19,434
You know the publishing industry
has been rough these days.

329
00:25:19,935 --> 00:25:22,521
But your book is bucking the trend.

330
00:25:22,604 --> 00:25:25,607
We'll need aggressive promo
to keep the momentum

331
00:25:25,690 --> 00:25:27,317
and we'll need your help.

332
00:25:27,901 --> 00:25:29,694
I'll do whatever I can to help.

333
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:31,071
Great.

334
00:25:31,154 --> 00:25:33,406
I'll green-light
the booking requests, then.

335
00:25:33,490 --> 00:25:34,491
Sure.

336
00:25:34,574 --> 00:25:36,535
We're moving in one minute.

337
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:37,869
Get ready, everyone.

338
00:25:38,286 --> 00:25:40,956
It's gotten busy here
with that drama shoot.

339
00:25:41,039 --> 00:25:43,833
You must come here often
to have picked this place.

340
00:25:43,917 --> 00:25:45,085
Sorry for the hassle.

341
00:25:45,168 --> 00:25:47,045
No, I picked it on purpose.

342
00:25:47,128 --> 00:25:48,421
I wanted to take a look.

343
00:25:49,005 --> 00:25:52,050
Oh, is it for your next book?

344
00:25:52,133 --> 00:25:56,471
Then the TV promo will help
with your writing.

345
00:25:57,138 --> 00:25:58,473
I think so.

346
00:25:58,557 --> 00:26:00,475
- Shall we head out?
- Yes.

347
00:26:13,613 --> 00:26:16,157
Sorry, did I keep you waiting?

348
00:26:16,241 --> 00:26:17,242
No, it's fine.

349
00:26:18,285 --> 00:26:19,953
- Director, I'm here.
- Was traffic bad?

350
00:26:20,036 --> 00:26:21,329
Parking took forever.

351
00:26:21,788 --> 00:26:23,123
Did you wait long?

352
00:26:26,293 --> 00:26:27,294
Look.

353
00:26:27,836 --> 00:26:28,920
We need to talk.

354
00:26:31,715 --> 00:26:32,716
Let's talk outside.

355
00:26:38,054 --> 00:26:39,055
Cut!

356
00:26:40,015 --> 00:26:41,016
One more time.

357
00:26:42,642 --> 00:26:44,060
- Gather up!
- Everyone, gather!

358
00:26:45,478 --> 00:26:46,646
Quickly!

359
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:49,649
That was great,
but we need more movement.

360
00:27:09,961 --> 00:27:10,962
Jun-seo.

361
00:27:20,055 --> 00:27:21,514
I finally tracked you down

362
00:27:22,057 --> 00:27:25,644
and you're still clinging to Ah-jin,
who treats you less than a rat?

363
00:27:26,186 --> 00:27:27,979
You're pathetic!

364
00:27:31,274 --> 00:27:32,275
"Still"?

365
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:36,780
So, there was something
between him and Baek Ah-jin before?

366
00:27:38,573 --> 00:27:39,574
Get off me.

367
00:27:40,784 --> 00:27:42,202
When did you get back?

368
00:27:42,285 --> 00:27:44,454
When you get back,
you call your mother first.

369
00:27:44,537 --> 00:27:46,331
Do I have to find out
from your advertisement?

370
00:27:46,414 --> 00:27:48,708
Why is it so hard
to see my own son's face?

371
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:52,837
Did you keep your promise to me?

372
00:27:54,214 --> 00:27:55,215
What promise?

373
00:27:55,298 --> 00:27:57,634
To apologize to Ah-jin.

374
00:27:58,009 --> 00:28:00,970
How long are you going to pretend
nothing happened?

375
00:28:01,721 --> 00:28:03,973
She ended up miserable,
all because of you.

376
00:28:05,684 --> 00:28:06,976
I can barely stand

377
00:28:08,103 --> 00:28:09,562
to look at you.

378
00:28:21,950 --> 00:28:22,951
Lena.

379
00:28:23,827 --> 00:28:24,869
What are you doing here?

380
00:28:25,161 --> 00:28:26,496
Introduce me to this author.

381
00:28:27,747 --> 00:28:28,748
Sorry?

382
00:28:28,832 --> 00:28:32,752
I'll post on Instagram and everywhere
that I loved his book.

383
00:28:32,836 --> 00:28:34,254
I don't care
if it's on TV or the radio.

384
00:28:34,337 --> 00:28:37,424
We can tell them to make a segment
like "Meet the Author."

385
00:28:38,883 --> 00:28:40,218
Why the sudden interest?

386
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:42,429
My soju deal is gone

387
00:28:42,512 --> 00:28:44,556
so I can hand back
the "Korea's Little Sister" title.

388
00:28:46,516 --> 00:28:49,352
I think it's time to rebrand
as sophisticated and intellectual.

389
00:28:50,437 --> 00:28:51,855
So, are you doing it or not?

390
00:28:53,148 --> 00:28:54,149
This is your job.

391
00:28:55,567 --> 00:28:57,569
I'll make some calls now.

392
00:29:00,488 --> 00:29:02,282
I am Ah-jin's mother.

393
00:29:02,365 --> 00:29:04,617
You still need to call ahead--

394
00:29:04,701 --> 00:29:07,245
What mother calls ahead?

395
00:29:07,328 --> 00:29:10,165
- You can't just barge in--
- Quiet.

396
00:29:10,248 --> 00:29:12,917
- Where's the CEO's office?
- What?

397
00:29:13,001 --> 00:29:14,252
Ah-jin's mother?

398
00:29:17,380 --> 00:29:20,383
As far as I know,
her mother passed away.

399
00:29:21,926 --> 00:29:23,511
I guess she hasn't told you.

400
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:27,056
I was her stepmother,
but I raised her with love.

401
00:29:28,183 --> 00:29:31,186
I fed her well
and gave her a good bed

402
00:29:31,269 --> 00:29:32,645
as if she were my own child.

403
00:29:32,729 --> 00:29:33,980
Yes, I heard.

404
00:29:35,398 --> 00:29:37,942
You lovingly raised her
and threw her out.

405
00:29:38,026 --> 00:29:39,027
She said that?

406
00:29:39,527 --> 00:29:41,112
She left on her own.

407
00:29:42,572 --> 00:29:43,573
Why are you here?

408
00:29:44,115 --> 00:29:46,284
Keep her off TV.

409
00:29:47,744 --> 00:29:48,912
Let me live.

410
00:29:49,204 --> 00:29:50,914
You know that's impossible.

411
00:29:51,206 --> 00:29:52,415
What do you really want?

412
00:29:54,709 --> 00:29:55,794
Money?

413
00:30:02,634 --> 00:30:04,135
I have money.

414
00:30:07,931 --> 00:30:09,140
Hello.

415
00:30:09,224 --> 00:30:10,433
Ah-jin.

416
00:30:10,517 --> 00:30:12,018
Your mother is here.

417
00:30:12,101 --> 00:30:13,770
Her, an actress?

418
00:30:15,188 --> 00:30:16,189
Don't make me laugh.

419
00:30:16,272 --> 00:30:20,443
She's not the type to wear
nice clothes and soak up applause.

420
00:30:20,527 --> 00:30:23,112
She's lowborn by nature.

421
00:30:23,196 --> 00:30:25,031
An alcoholic for a mother

422
00:30:25,114 --> 00:30:27,200
and a criminal for a father.

423
00:30:27,283 --> 00:30:28,910
What more do you need to know?

424
00:30:29,702 --> 00:30:30,703
Excuse me?

425
00:30:31,204 --> 00:30:34,833
Do you know how her father died?

426
00:30:36,918 --> 00:30:38,211
He was killed.

427
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:41,631
Someone else served time,
but I know the truth.

428
00:30:42,799 --> 00:30:45,718
Ah-jin did it.

429
00:30:49,138 --> 00:30:52,016
Just thinking about it
makes my heart race

430
00:30:52,559 --> 00:30:53,560
and terrifies me.

431
00:30:54,394 --> 00:30:57,188
And now, she's on TV everywhere

432
00:30:57,272 --> 00:30:59,440
so I'm too scared

433
00:31:00,233 --> 00:31:01,568
to even breathe.

434
00:31:06,155 --> 00:31:10,326
It's best you stay away
from that bitch.

435
00:31:10,410 --> 00:31:12,370
Ignore me if you want

436
00:31:13,204 --> 00:31:16,791
but you'll see what I mean
once she devours you.

437
00:31:16,875 --> 00:31:20,712
Most people only get it
after she's taken an arm

438
00:31:21,462 --> 00:31:24,632
because of how cunning she is.

439
00:31:32,140 --> 00:31:33,141
Long time no see.

440
00:31:33,766 --> 00:31:34,809
How have you been?

441
00:31:34,893 --> 00:31:35,894
Great, thanks to you.

442
00:31:35,977 --> 00:31:39,439
Since you beat me everywhere
but the face to put me on camera.

443
00:31:39,522 --> 00:31:40,565
Why are you here?

444
00:31:40,648 --> 00:31:41,941
I'm not here to see you.

445
00:31:42,817 --> 00:31:44,485
I came so I won't have to see you
ever again.

446
00:31:48,573 --> 00:31:50,283
I hope you get my drift.

447
00:31:50,825 --> 00:31:52,410
Let's not meet again.

448
00:32:01,669 --> 00:32:04,130
Sorry about that.
That must have been unpleasant.

449
00:32:05,131 --> 00:32:07,508
It wasn't fun, but I'm used to it.

450
00:32:08,301 --> 00:32:10,303
It's also my job
to handle these things.

451
00:32:10,386 --> 00:32:13,514
And it's the reason
you need to earn well.

452
00:32:15,391 --> 00:32:16,809
I understand.

453
00:32:17,977 --> 00:32:20,855
I'll climb steadily
so this doesn't happen again.

454
00:32:28,738 --> 00:32:31,032
What kind of life have you lived?

455
00:32:31,741 --> 00:32:34,243
Even your own mother
isn't on your side.

456
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:41,334
Your past must be fascinating.

457
00:32:42,168 --> 00:32:43,336
I'm dying to know.

458
00:32:45,296 --> 00:32:46,756
If you keep this up

459
00:32:47,382 --> 00:32:50,426
you'll only end up more upset.

460
00:32:55,014 --> 00:32:57,308
- Are you worried for me?
- Yes.

461
00:32:58,851 --> 00:33:02,605
Because I want you to keep working
in this field for a long time.

462
00:33:03,272 --> 00:33:04,691
Worry about yourself.

463
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:08,403
I'm busy figuring out
what'll finally make me feel better.

464
00:33:11,406 --> 00:33:12,407
Look forward to it.

465
00:33:25,503 --> 00:33:27,922
SPECIAL GUESTS
AUTHOR YOON SEOK-HA, ACTRESS LENA

466
00:33:31,426 --> 00:33:32,635
Hey, Lena.

467
00:33:33,344 --> 00:33:36,055
This is the author
you'll be appearing with. Say hi.

468
00:33:38,516 --> 00:33:40,935
- Nice to meet you.
- Pleasure to meet you.

469
00:33:41,310 --> 00:33:43,271
You're really handsome for an author.

470
00:33:43,855 --> 00:33:45,064
Thank you.

471
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:47,275
Do you have a girlfriend?

472
00:33:48,359 --> 00:33:49,360
Or you had one?

473
00:33:50,361 --> 00:33:51,779
Someone you can't get over?

474
00:33:55,491 --> 00:33:56,492
I'm joking.

475
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:58,828
Do you want to grab dinner after?

476
00:33:59,454 --> 00:34:01,706
No, thank you.

477
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:07,712
We'll bring you both in together
in five minutes.

478
00:34:09,441 --> 00:34:21,441
Officail Website : kissasian.be  Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

479
00:34:11,466 --> 00:34:13,843
CO-OFFENDER Y

480
00:34:13,926 --> 00:34:15,928
"'Let me find the highest place.

481
00:34:17,055 --> 00:34:19,390
Let every moment become a chance

482
00:34:20,266 --> 00:34:21,559
to paint myself.

483
00:34:24,228 --> 00:34:26,898
And let my finished portrait hang

484
00:34:28,107 --> 00:34:29,984
at the very top of the world.'

485
00:34:31,611 --> 00:34:32,862
This was her prayer

486
00:34:33,529 --> 00:34:36,032
and I prayed it wouldn't be answered.

487
00:34:37,992 --> 00:34:39,952
I prayed that the child
I failed to save

488
00:34:40,787 --> 00:34:42,914
somehow escaped the savagery

489
00:34:44,123 --> 00:34:47,293
and now rests in quiet days."

490
00:34:47,627 --> 00:34:50,254
Okay, I got it.

491
00:34:50,797 --> 00:34:52,173
Ah-jin, you must be hungry.

492
00:34:53,132 --> 00:34:55,760
- Who was that on the phone?
- The agency.

493
00:34:55,843 --> 00:34:57,428
There will be
a building inspection today.

494
00:34:57,512 --> 00:35:00,098
Power's out from six o'clock,
so everyone's heading home early.

495
00:35:00,848 --> 00:35:02,183
Great work, everyone.

496
00:35:02,266 --> 00:35:03,893
- Great work.
- Thank you.

497
00:35:03,976 --> 00:35:06,187
You two were fantastic.

498
00:35:06,270 --> 00:35:08,981
- The live reactions were amazing.
- That's great.

499
00:35:09,065 --> 00:35:10,066
- See you next time.
- Yes.

500
00:35:10,149 --> 00:35:11,526
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

501
00:35:13,444 --> 00:35:14,946
If dinner's a no, do you like drinks?

502
00:35:17,365 --> 00:35:18,366
- Hong-sik.
- Yes?

503
00:35:18,449 --> 00:35:21,160
He's taking me home tonight,
so you can clock out first.

504
00:35:21,244 --> 00:35:22,245
Okay.

505
00:35:23,996 --> 00:35:24,997
I can't drive.

506
00:35:25,706 --> 00:35:27,041
Be my chauffeur.

507
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:29,418
Are you bored, or just naturally--

508
00:35:29,502 --> 00:35:30,586
Naturally a psycho?

509
00:35:31,337 --> 00:35:32,547
Think whatever you want.

510
00:35:34,173 --> 00:35:35,633
I'll wait on the first floor.

511
00:35:45,393 --> 00:35:46,394
Hyang-i.

512
00:35:47,436 --> 00:35:48,437
You must be tired.

513
00:35:50,314 --> 00:35:53,860
Don't you have to take the car back
to the office after you drop me off?

514
00:35:55,194 --> 00:35:56,362
You know what?

515
00:35:57,321 --> 00:35:59,991
Just let me off there,
then go straight home.

516
00:36:00,867 --> 00:36:02,535
It's fine. I'm okay.

517
00:36:03,077 --> 00:36:07,373
And if I drop you off at the office,
how will you get home?

518
00:36:08,332 --> 00:36:09,834
That's what taxis are for.

519
00:36:11,210 --> 00:36:13,212
You said everyone left early, anyway.

520
00:36:13,296 --> 00:36:15,673
You should go home and get some rest.

521
00:36:16,299 --> 00:36:17,592
Should I?

522
00:36:29,270 --> 00:36:30,438
HYANG-I

523
00:36:33,024 --> 00:36:36,861
I'LL TELL HER
THE BUILDING WILL BE UNDER INSPECTION

524
00:36:38,237 --> 00:36:39,238
Actually

525
00:36:40,198 --> 00:36:41,741
I should swing by the office.

526
00:36:42,825 --> 00:36:45,244
I left something really important.

527
00:36:45,328 --> 00:36:46,537
Mind if I go grab it?

